      <section eId="sec_CCRP-596">
        <num>CCRP 596</num>
        <heading>596. Â Requirements for double jeopardy</heading>
        <subsection eId="CCRP-596__subsec_1">
          <num>(1)</num>
          <content>
            <p>Identical with or a different grade of the same offense for which the defendant was in jeopardy in the first trial, whether or not a responsive verdict could have been rendered in the first trial as to the charge in the second trial; or</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="CCRP-596__subsec_2">
          <num>(2)</num>
          <content>
            <p>Based on a part of a continuous offense for which offense the defendant was in jeopardy in the first trial.</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <authorialNote marker="source">
          <p>Source: https://www.legis.la.gov/legis/Law.aspx?d=112639</p>
        </authorialNote>
      </section>
